# 📧 Spam Email Classifier using Machine Learning

A Machine Learning-based Spam Email Classification System that automatically identifies whether an email is **Spam** or **Ham (Not Spam)** using Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques and classification algorithms.

## 🚀 Features

- Email text preprocessing
- TF-IDF feature extraction
- Spam/Ham classification
- Naive Bayes Model
- Logistic Regression Model
- Model accuracy comparison
- Confusion Matrix visualization
- Real-time email prediction
- Performance evaluation metrics

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-Learn
- Matplotlib
- NLP
- TF-IDF Vectorization

## 📂 Dataset

The project uses a real-world email dataset containing:

- 5,728 Emails
- Spam Emails
- Ham (Legitimate) Emails

Dataset Source:
https://github.com/OmkarPathak/Playing-with-datasets

## ⚙️ Machine Learning Workflow

1. Data Collection
2. Data Preprocessing
3. Text Cleaning
4. TF-IDF Vectorization
5. Train-Test Split
6. Model Training
7. Model Evaluation
8. Prediction and Visualization

## 🤖 Algorithms Used

### Naive Bayes
- Fast and efficient text classification
- Suitable for spam detection

### Logistic Regression
- High classification accuracy
- Effective binary classification

## 📊 Evaluation Metrics

The following metrics are used:

- Accuracy Score
- Precision
- Recall
- F1 Score
- Confusion Matrix

## 📈 Output

The system generates:

- Classification Report
- Model Accuracy Comparison
- Confusion Matrix
- Spam Probability Prediction

Example:

Email:
"Congratulations! You've won $1,000,000"

Prediction:
Spam ✅

---

Email:
"Meeting rescheduled to 4 PM"

Prediction:
Ham ✅

## 📁 Project Structure

```
Spam-Email-Classifier/
│
├── spam_email_classifier.py
├── spam_classifier_results.png
├── README.md
└── requirements.txt
```

## ▶️ How to Run

### Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Spam-Email-Classifier.git
```

### Navigate to Project Folder

```bash
cd Spam-Email-Classifier
```

### Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Run Project

```bash
python spam_email_classifier.py
```

## 📷 Sample Output

The application provides:

- Email Classification
- Spam Probability
- Accuracy Comparison Chart
- Confusion Matrix Visualization

